Survival analysis by TP53 and telomerase activity

This notebook will do the following survival analysis 1. Univariant analysis - TP53 classifier score (as a continuous variable) - EXTEND score (as a continuous variable) - Cancer group, removing cancer groups with less than 10 samples - HGG vs. non-HGG

  1. Multivariant analysis
  • TP53 classifier score, EXTEND score and whatever disease label we determine is appropriate
  1. Plots
  • Probably a forest plot will be generated to display the information.

                         "independent-specimens.rnaseq.primary-plus-stranded.tsv")

 mutate(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID_RNA = SampleID,
        telomerase_score = NormEXTENDScores) %>%

# remove samples without RNA-Seq since both classifiers' results use RNA-Seq
# independent use primary plus rna-seq samples
meta_indep <- tp53_scores %>%
  left_join(tel_scores) %>%
  left_join(histologies) %>%
  dplyr::filter(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID_RNA %in% indep_rna$Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID) %>%
  # recode the categories
  dplyr::mutate(OS_status_fixed = case_when(
    OS_status == "LIVING" ~ 0,
    OS_status == "DECEASED" ~1
 ))
Joining, by = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID_RNA"
Joining, by = "sample_id"

Cox Regression

TP53 scores & Telomerase score - results

# run the model with different covariates
for(ind_var in c("tp53_score", "telomerase_score")){
  model <- paste0("survival::Surv(OS_days, OS_status_fixed) ~ ", ind_var)
  
  fit <- survival::coxph(
        formula(model),
        data = meta_indep
      )
  # generate output
  table <- broom::tidy(fit) 
  
  # Save the table data in a TSV
  readr::write_tsv(table, file.path(results_dir, paste0("cox_reg_results_per_", ind_var, ".tsv")))
  
  print(table)
}

Log Rank analysis

Categorical variable cancer group and HGG or not

# separate into HGG or non-HGG
meta_indep <- meta_indep %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(hgg_group = case_when(
    short_histology == "HGAT" ~ "HGAT",
    short_histology != "HGAT" ~ "non-HGAT"
  ))

# filter to contain only samples in short histology that that have >=10 samples
meta_indep_sh_filtered <- meta_indep %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(short_histology) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(n_cg = n()) %>% 
  dplyr::filter(n_cg >=10)

Generate output for categorical files

ind_var_list <- c("hgg_group", "short_histology")
meta_data_list <- list(meta_indep, meta_indep_sh_filtered)

for(i in 1:length(ind_var_list)){
  ind_var <- ind_var_list[i]
  meta_data <- meta_data_list[[i]]
  
  # define model
  model <- paste0("survival::Surv(OS_days, OS_status_fixed) ~ ", ind_var)
  
  # run survival analysis
  fit <- survival::survdiff(formula(model),
                            data = meta_data)
  # Obtain p value for Chi-Squared stat
  fit$p.value <- pchisq(fit$chisq, df = 1, lower = FALSE)
  
  print(fit)
  # save the output
  saveRDS(fit, file.path(results_dir, paste0("log_rank_survival_per_", ind_var, ".RDS")))
  
  # generate plots fit
  fit_plot <- survfit(formula(model), data = meta_data)
  plot_coxph <- survminer::ggsurvplot(fit_plot,
                                      data=meta_data,
                                      xlim = c(0, 5000),
                                      break.time.by = 500,
                                      pval = TRUE, 
                                      conf.int = TRUE,
                                      risk.table = TRUE, # Add risk table
                                      risk.table.col = "strata", # Change risk table color by groups
                                      linetype = "strata", # Change line type by groups
                                      surv.median.line = "hv", # Specify median survival
                                      ggtheme = theme_bw()) # Change ggplot2 theme
  
  # Make this plot a combined plot
  surv_plot_coxph <- cowplot::plot_grid(plot_coxph[[1]], 
                                        plot_coxph[[2]], 
                                        nrow = 2, 
                                        rel_heights = c(2.5, 2.5))
  
  print(surv_plot_coxph)
  
  # Save the plot
  cowplot::save_plot(filename = file.path(plots_dir, paste0("coxph_survival_per_", ind_var, ".png")), plot = surv_plot_coxph)
}
